Powerhouse Eddie &apos;The Beast&apos; Hall has been crowned Britain&apos;s Strongest Man for the fourth year in a row. 

The 28-year-old Clayton strongman took part in the competition on Saturday at the Doncaster Dome. 

 
The largely British line up of strongmen saw the champions of England, Scotland, Wales, Northern Ireland and other guest nations go head-to-head for three golden places at the World&apos;s Strongest Man finals of 2017. 
 
